 We know the car in the fast lane traveled 480 miles in 60 hours. First, we need to convert the speed from miles per hour to miles per hour. Since 1 mile = 1.60934 kilometers, we convert 60 miles to kilometers 60 \text{ miles} \times 1.60934 \text{ km/mile} = 96.6 \text{ km} 
Since the car in the slow lane travels half of the speed of the car in the fast lane, we can set up a proportion to find the time taken by the car in the slow lane to cover the same distance. Let x be the time taken by the car in the slow lane. Then, the ratio of the distances traveled by the two cars is 96.6 km / x km. We know that the car in the fast lane traveled 480 miles in 60 hours, so we can set up the equation 96.6/x = 480/60 
