 We know that the 4 girls are 64", the 3 girls are 60", and the shortest girl is 60". Since the human pyramid is built on the principle of height, we can add the heights of all the girls together and then add the height of the shortest girl to get the total height of the pyramid. 

First, we add the heights of the 4 girls \text{Total height of the 4} = 64 + 64 + 60 + 60 = 248 \text{ inches} 

Next, we add the heights of the 3 girls on top of the 4 \text{Total height of the 3} = 60 + 60 + 60 + 60 = 300 \text{ inches} 

Then, we add the height of the shortest girl, who is 60", to the total height of the 3 \text{Total height of the 3 and the shortest girl} = 300 + 60 = 360 \text{ inches} 

Finally, we add the height of the 2 girls on top of the 3 to the total height of the 3 and the shortest girl \text{Total height of the 2} = 60 + 60 = 120 \text{ inches} 

Now, we add the total height of the 4, the 3, and the 2 to get the total height of the human pyramid \text{Total height of the human pyramid} = 248 + 300 + 360 + 120 = 1,008 \text{ inches} 

To convert inches to feet, we divide by 12 since there are 12 inches in a foot \text{Total height of the human pyramid in feet} = \frac{1,008}{12} \approx 84.52 \text{ feet} 

Therefore, the human pyramid is approximately 84.52 feet tall.
