 First, we need to find the area of the rectangle. The formula for the area of a rectangle is length times width. Here, the length is 20 feet and the width is 15 feet. 

 \text{Area} = \text{length} \times \text{width} 
 \text{Area} = 20 \text{ ft} \times 15 \text{ ft} 
 \text{Area} = 300 \text{ ft}^2 

Since we want the number of feet of crepe paper, not the area, we'll use the perimeter formula, which is the sum of all sides. The perimeter of a rectangle is the sum of all sides. Since the fence is a rectangle, we add 20 + 15 = 35 feet to the length and 35 + 15 = 50 feet to the width.

 \text{Perimeter} = 2 \times (\text{length} + \text{width}) 
 \text{Perimeter} = 2 \times (35 \text{ ft} + 15 \text{ ft}) 
 \text{Perimeter} = 2 \times 50 \text{ ft} 
 \text{Perimeter} = 100 \text{ ft} 

Therefore, James needs 100 feet of crepe paper to hang the streamers.
The answer is: 100 ft

